{"title_page": "Tonic (2020 film)", "text_new": "{{copyedit|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Tonic\n| image          = \n| alt            = \n| caption        = \n| film_name      = <!-- {{Infobox name module|language|title}} or {{Infobox name module|title}} -->\n| director       = Avijit Sen\n| producer       = Bengal Talkies \n| writer         = \n| screenplay     = \n| story          = \n| based_on       = <!-- {{Based on|title of the original work|creator of the original work|additional creator(s), if necessary}} -->\n| starring       = [[#Cast|See below]]\n| narrator       = \n| music          = [[Jeet Ganguly]] \n| cinematography = Supriyo Dutta \n| editing        = Sujay Dutta Ray\n| studio         = <!-- or: | production_companies = -->\n| distributor    = Bengal Talkies \n| released       = <!-- {{Film date|df=yes/no|year|month|day|location|ref1=}} -->\n| runtime        = \n| country        = [[India]] \n| language       = [[Bengali]]\n| budget         = \n| gross          = \n}}\nTonic is a 2020 Indian [[Bengali]] [[Drama (film and television)|Drama Film]] directed by Avijit Sen and produced by Atanu Raychudhuri.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bengali/movies/news/tonic-teaser-creates-a-buzz/articleshow/74570640.cms|title=\u2018Tonic\u2019 teaser creates a buzz - Times of India|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bengali/movies/previews/tonic/articleshow/74592360.cms|title=\u2018Tonic\u2019 - Times of India|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> This film will be released this year, under the Banner of Bengal Talkies. \n\n== Plot ==\nTonic<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cinestaan.com/articles/2020/feb/20/24610|title=Dev Adhikari, Paran Bandopadhyay to star in Avijit Sen's Tonic|last=Sarkar|first=Roushni|website=Cinestaan|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> is the movie that tells us the story of 75 yrs old retired Jaladhar Sen who lives with his wife, son, daughter-in-law and granddaughter. The old couple is troubled by the neglect shown by the family and their misery aggravates when their 46<sup>th</sup> marriage anniversary celebration is planned to be just a small get-together. Jaladhar plans for a foreign trip and this dream brings him to a travel agent named Tonic who later turns out to be a miracle maker in life. The foreign trip and even the Darjeeling trip gets cancelled due to Jaladhar\u2019s sudden illness but it is the magical presence of Tonic that brings back the lost happiness and love in the family.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/videos/entertainment/events/kolkata/glimpses-from-the-poster-launch-of-the-film-tonic/videoshow/74169183.cms|title=Glimpses from the poster launch of the film Tonic {{!}} Entertainment - Times of India Videos|website=timesofindia.indiatimes.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.spotboye.com/bengali/bengali-news/tonic-actor-dev-adhikari-releases-first-poster-of-his-next-film/5e4a20003a53c04ab842f2e7|title=Tonic: Actor Dev Adhikari Releases First Poster Of His Next Film|last=SpotboyE|website=www.spotboye.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>\n<br />\n\n== Cast ==\n\n* [[Dev (Bengali actor)|Dev]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bengali/movies/news/dev-blessed-to-share-the-screen-with-paran-bandopadhyay-and-shakuntala-barua/articleshow/74278717.cms|title=Dev blessed to share the screen with Paran Bandopadhyay and Shakuntala Barua - Times of India|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> As Tonic\n* \u00a0[[Paran Bandopadhyay]] as Jaladhar Sen\n* [[Shakuntala Barua]] \n* [[Sujan Mukhopadhyay]] \n* [[Biswanath Basu]] \n* [[Koneenica Banerjee]]\n* [[Rajatava Dutta]] \n* [[Tanusree Chakraborty]] \n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External Link ==\n* {{IMDb title|tt11941700}}\n\n[[Category:2020 films]]\n\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:2020 films]]\n[[Category:Bengali-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian drama films]]\n[[Category:Indian drama films]]\n", "text_old": "{{copyedit|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Tonic\n| image          = \n| alt            = \n| caption        = \n| film_name      = <!-- {{Infobox name module|language|title}} or {{Infobox name module|title}} -->\n| director       = Avijit Sen\n| producer       = Bengal Talkies \n| writer         = \n| screenplay     = \n| story          = \n| based_on       = <!-- {{Based on|title of the original work|creator of the original work|additional creator(s), if necessary}} -->\n| starring       = [[#Cast|See below]]\n| narrator       = \n| music          = [[Jeet Ganguly]] \n| cinematography = Supriyo Dutta \n| editing        = Sujay Dutta Ray\n| studio         = <!-- or: | production_companies = -->\n| distributor    = Bengal Talkies \n| released       = <!-- {{Film date|df=yes/no|year|month|day|location|ref1=}} -->\n| runtime        = \n| country        = [[India]] \n| language       = [[Bengali]]\n| budget         = \n| gross          = \n}}\nTonic is a 2020 Indian [[Bengali]] [[Drama (film and television)|Drama Film]] directed by Avijit Sen and produced by Atanu Raychudhuri.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bengali/movies/news/tonic-teaser-creates-a-buzz/articleshow/74570640.cms|title=\u2018Tonic\u2019 teaser creates a buzz - Times of India|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bengali/movies/previews/tonic/articleshow/74592360.cms|title=\u2018Tonic\u2019 - Times of India|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> This film will be released this year, under the Banner of Bengal Talkies. \n\n== Plot ==\nTonic<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cinestaan.com/articles/2020/feb/20/24610|title=Dev Adhikari, Paran Bandopadhyay to star in Avijit Sen's Tonic|last=Sarkar|first=Roushni|website=Cinestaan|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> is the movie that tells us the story of 75 yrs old retired Jaladhar Sen who lives with his wife, son, daughter-in-law and granddaughter. The old couple is troubled by the neglect shown by the family and their misery aggravates when their 46<sup>th</sup> marriage anniversary celebration is planned to be just a small get-together. Jaladhar plans for a foreign trip and this dream brings him to a travel agent named Tonic who later turns out to be a miracle maker in life. The foreign trip and even the Darjeeling trip gets cancelled due to Jaladhar\u2019s sudden illness but it is the magical presence of Tonic that brings back the lost happiness and love in the family.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/videos/entertainment/events/kolkata/glimpses-from-the-poster-launch-of-the-film-tonic/videoshow/74169183.cms|title=Glimpses from the poster launch of the film Tonic {{!}} Entertainment - Times of India Videos|website=timesofindia.indiatimes.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.spotboye.com/bengali/bengali-news/tonic-actor-dev-adhikari-releases-first-poster-of-his-next-film/5e4a20003a53c04ab842f2e7|title=Tonic: Actor Dev Adhikari Releases First Poster Of His Next Film|last=SpotboyE|website=www.spotboye.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref>\n<br />\n\n== Cast ==\n\n* [[Dev (Bengali actor)|Dev]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bengali/movies/news/dev-blessed-to-share-the-screen-with-paran-bandopadhyay-and-shakuntala-barua/articleshow/74278717.cms|title=Dev blessed to share the screen with Paran Bandopadhyay and Shakuntala Barua - Times of India|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> As Tonic\n* \u00a0[[Paran Bandopadhyay]] as Jaladhar Sen\n* [[Shakuntala Barua]] \n* [[Sujan Mukhopadhyay