osters (season 4)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 82\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 20\n| Title           = Until Tomorrow\n| DirectedBy      = Peter Paige\n| WrittenBy       = Bradley Bredeweg & Peter Paige\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|2017|4|11}}\n| ShortSummary    = Callie is pressured to take a plea deal, which would result in her going to jail for three years. Stef and Mike look into the evidence and other footage again to see if they clear Callie. They end up concluding that Troy was most likely the murderer after all and get him to confess. However, when Callie tries to stop another girl from leaving with Diamond to go visit Russell, she offers herself up instead. Meanwhile, Jesus questions various people to try and get confirmation about Emma's pregnancy and his grandmother tells him what was in the missing letter. At the end of the episode, Daphne shows up at the home to let Stef know about Callie's whereabouts, while Callie is now in a hotel room alone with Russell. \n| Viewers         = 0.72<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-tuesday-cable-originals-network-finals-4-11-2017.html|title=Updated: ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Tuesday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 4.11.2017|last=Metcalf|first=Mitch|accessdate=April 12, 2017|work=Showbuzz Daily|date=April 12, 2017}}</ref>\n| LineColor       = 802A2A\n}}\n}}</onlyinclude>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fosters (season 4), The}}\n[[Category:2016 American television seasons]] \n[[Category:2017 American television seasons]]\n[[Category:The Fosters (2013 TV series)]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox television season\n| season_number = 4\n| bgcolour      = #802A2A\n| image         = The Fosters season 4 poster.jpg\n| caption       = ''The Fosters'' season 4 poster\n| starring       = {{Plain list|\n* [[Teri Polo]]\n* [[Sherri Saum]]\n* [[Hayden Byerly]]\n* [[David Lambert (actor)|David Lambert]]\n* [[Maia Mitchell]]\n* [[Danny Nucci]]\n* [[Cierra Ramirez]]\n* [[Noah Centineo]]\n}}\n| country       = United States\n| num_episodes  = 20\n| network       = [[Freeform (TV channel)|Freeform]]\n| first_aired   = {{Start date|2016|6|20}}\n| last_aired    = {{End date|2017|4|11}}\n| episode_list  = List of The Fosters episodes\n| prev_season   = [[The Fosters (season 3)|Season 3]]\n| next_season   = [[The Fosters (season 5)|Season 5]]\n}}\n\nThe fourth season of ''[[The Fosters (American TV series)|The Fosters]]'' premiered on June 20, 2016 and ended on April 11, 2017. The season consisted of 20 episodes and stars [[Teri Polo]] and [[Sherri Saum]] as Stef Foster and Lena Adams, an interracial lesbian couple, who foster a girl, Callie  ([[Maia Mitchell]]) and her younger brother, Jude ([[Hayden Byerly]]) while also trying to juggle raising [[Latino]] twin teenagers, Mariana and Jesus  ([[Cierra Ramirez]] and [[Noah Centineo]]), and Stef's biological son, Brandon ([[David Lambert (actor)|David Lambert]]). In this season, Callie is determined to find out about a police case who convicted a teenager of murder but learns the dark secrets surrounding the case. Meanwhile, after adopting AJ, Mike struggles with fatherhood while dealing with his girlfriend, Ana. Also, Mariana struggles to let go of Nick ([[Louis Hunter]]) after the incident at school.\n\n==Cast==\n{{main|List of The Fosters characters}}\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-3}}\n\n===Main cast===\n* [[Teri Polo]] as Stef Adams Foster\n* [[Sherri Saum]] as Lena Adams Foster\n* [[Noah Centineo]] as Jesus Adams Foster\n* [[Hayden Byerly]] as Jude Adams Foster\n* [[David Lambert (actor)|David Lambert]] as Brandon Foster\n* [[Maia Mitchell]] as Callie Adams Foster\n* [[Cierra Ramirez]] as Mariana Adams Foster\n* [[Danny Nucci]] as Mike Foster\n{{col-3}}\n\n===Recurring cast===\n* [[Tom Williamson (actor)|Tom Williamson]] as AJ Hensdale\n* [[Jordan Rodrigues]] as Mat Tan\n* [[Elliot Fletcher]] as Aaron Baker\n* [[Amanda Leighton]] as Emma\n* Kalama Epstein as Noah\n* [[Izabela Vidovic]] as Taylor\n* [[Louis Hunter]] as Nick Stratos\n* [[Annika Marks]] as Monte Porter\n* [[Denyse Tontz]] as Cortney Strathmore\n* [[Brandon Quinn]] as Gabriel Duncroft\n* [[Kerr Smith]] as Robert Quinn\n* [[Alexandra Barreto]] as Ana Gutierrez\n* [[Alex Skuby]] as Joe Gray\n* Hugh Scott as Doug Harvey\n* Levi Fiehler as Troy Johnson\n* Daffany Clark as Daphne Keene\n* Mark Totty as Craig Stratos\n* Jared Ward as Drew Turner\n* [[Michael Traynor (actor)|Michael Traynor]] as Craig \n* [[Adam Irigoyen]] as Kyle Snow\n* Meg DeLacy as Grace Mullen\n* Hope Olaid\u00e9 Wilson as Diamond\n{{col-3}}\n\n===Guest cast===\n* [[Annie Potts]] as Sharon Elkin\n* [[Rob Morrow]] as Will\n* [[Lorraine Toussaint]] as Dana Adams\n* [[Bruce Davison]] as Stuart Adams\n* [[Suzanne Cryer]] as Jenna Paul\n* [[Madisen Beaty]] as Talya Banks\n* [[Madison Pettis]] as Daria\n* [[Bailee Madison]] as Sophia Quinn \n* [[Ashley Argota]] as Lou Chan\n* [[April Parker Jones]] as Captain Roberts\n* Chad Todhunter as Patrick Molloy\n* Jay Ali as Timothy\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Episodes==\n{{see also|List of The Fosters episodes}}\n<onlyinclude>\n{{Episode table\n| background  = #802A2A\n| overall     = 5\n| season      = 5\n| title       = 20\n| director    = 14\n| writer      = 30\n| airdate     = 16\n| viewers     = 10\n| country     = US\n| episodes    =\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Fosters (season 4)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 63\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 1\n| Title           = Potential Energy\n| DirectedBy      = [[Rob Morrow]]\n| WrittenBy       = Bradley Bredeweg & [[Peter Paige]]\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2016|6|20}}\n| ShortSummary    = Anchor Beach is on lockdown when Mariana's boyfriend, Nick, enters the school with a gun after witnessing her kissing her ex, Mat. Meanwhile, Callie goes through the aftermath of having told her moms about her and Brandon.\n| Viewers         = 0.91<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2016/06/21/monday-cable-ratings-june-20-2016/|title=Monday cable ratings: \u2018Love & Hip H