ify\n| DirectedBy      = [[Kelli Williams]]\n| WrittenBy       = Cristian Martinez\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2016|8|1}}\n| ShortSummary    = Lena is pushed to the limit when she discovers secrets involving her parents, while Mariana gets pushed around by male STEM team members. Jesus wants to change his and Emma's relationship agreement, and Jude learns that Noah has a medical marijuana card. \n| Viewers         = 0.93<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-monday-cable-originals-network-finals-7-25-2016.html|title=Updated: ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Monday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 8.1.2016|last=Metcalf |first=Mitch|accessdate=August 3, 2016|work=ShowBuzzDaily|date=August 2, 2016}}</ref>\n| LineColor       = 802A2A\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Fosters (season 4)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 69\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 7\n| Title           = Highs and Lows\n| DirectedBy      = [[Chandra Wilson]]\n| WrittenBy       = Kris Q. Rehl\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2016|8|8}}\n| ShortSummary    = Whilst covering for Gabe when he doesn't turn up for work on the garage Jesus hits himself in the forehead with a nail gun. Callie tells Noah's mom about him giving Jude marijuana. Emma agrees to be Jesus's girlfriend again when they're in the hospital. Stef and Lena need to sell the house to pay back Lena's father. \n| Viewers         = 0.80<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-monday-cable-originals-network-finals-8-8-2016.html|title=Updated: ShowBuzzDaily's Top 150 Monday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 8.8.2016|last=Metcalf |first=Mitch|accessdate=August 9, 2016|work=ShowBuzzDaily|date=August 9, 2016}}</ref>\n| LineColor       = 802A2A\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|The Fosters (season 4)\n| EpisodeNumber   = 70\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 8\n| Title           = Girl Code\n| DirectedBy      = Aprill Winney\n| WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Dan Richter|t=Megan Lynn & Wade Solomon}}\n| Origi